# challenge
Orders

| order_id | customer_id | order_date | amount |

Write a SQL query to find the total amount spent by each customer and return the top 3 customers who spent the most money.

select customer_id, sum(amount) as total_amount from orders
group by customer_id
order by total_amount desc
limit 3

find the top 3 customers in each year.

with cte1 as (select customer_id, year(order_date)  as year, sum(amount) as total_amount
from orders
group by customer_id, year(order_date)),
cte2 as (select year, customer_id, total_amount, dense_rank() over (partition by year order by total_amount desc) as rn
from cte1)
select year, customer_id, total_amount from cte2 where rn <= 3






































